BIOGRAPHIES OF AUTHORS
Suratmi is currently a doctoral student at the Indonesian Education University Elementary School, Bandung. The author works as a lecturer at the Elementary School Teacher Education Study Program, Faculty of Teacher Training and Education, Sriwijaya University, Palembang. The author obtained a Bachelor's degree in Biology from Sriwijaya University, Indonesia in 2006, and completed a master's program in science education at an Indonesian education university in 2009. Currently, he is actively researching with the main research directions being primary school teacher education, science education, and RADEC learning. She can be contacted at email: Suratmi@fkip.unsi.ac.id.
Wahyu Sopandi completed his undergraduate education at the Department of Chemistry Education, FPMIPA IKIP Bandung, graduated in 1989 with, a master's degree in Early and Middle Childhood Education, Educational Theory and Practice, College of Education, Ohio State University, Columbus USA, graduated in 1995, and a doctorate at the Institut für Didatik der Chemie, Fachbereich Chemie and Pharmazie, University of Muenster, Germany, graduated in 2004. Since 2017 until now the author has served as Chair of the UPI SPs Basic Education Study Program. The author currently works as a lecturer at the undergraduate, postgraduate, and doctoral levels with expertise in the fields of Science Learning and Chemistry Learning. The author actively writes scientific papers in the form of books and journal articles as well as an assessor and reviewer of textbooks and non-texts for science and chemistry subjects at the Curriculum and Books Center of the Ministry of Education and Culture. The author is also active in conducting research and community service and as a resource person in some training activities, seminars, workshops, public lectures, and members of the ad hoc team in the preparation of some documents organized by the Ministry of Education and Culture. He can be contacted at email: wsopandi@upi.edu.